   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To support African Centre for Biosafety&apos;s (ACB) work in finding solutions to Africa&apos;s food insecurity by protecting Africa&apos;s agricultural biodiversity, traditional knowledge, and other ecological and social systems that are threatened by influx of GMOs and Green Revolution agricultural technologies. They will work with a range of partners on the continent to empower communities and organizations to make informed decisions and influence others to promote seed sovereignty and sustainable agricultural practices. With a loss of around 80% of the agricultural diversity in Africa, these efforts will help recover some of the traditional and sustainable farming techniques to prevent further loss and work for better food sovereignty</narrative>
